{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":637,"text":"I'm going to start with a little story."},{"time":2092,"text":"So, I grew up in this neighborhood. When I was 15 years old,"},{"time":5204,"text":"I went from being what I think was a strapping young athlete,"},{"time":9755,"text":"over four months, slowly wasting away until"},{"time":13716,"text":"I was basically a famine victim"},{"time":15604,"text":"with an unquenchable thirst."},{"time":17628,"text":"I had basically digested away my body."},{"time":21237,"text":"And this all came to a head when I was on a backpacking trip,"},{"time":25531,"text":"my first one ever actually, on Old Rag Mountain"},{"time":27576,"text":"in West Virginia, and was putting my face into puddles"},{"time":31560,"text":"of water and drinking like a dog."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33816,"text":"That night, I was taken into the emergency room"},{"time":38328,"text":"and diagnosed as a type 1 diabetic in full-blown ketoacidosis."},{"time":42209,"text":"And I recovered, thanks to the miracles of modern medicine,"},{"time":48144,"text":"insulin and other things, and gained all my weight back and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53600,"text":"And something festered inside me after this happened."},{"time":59111,"text":"What I thought about was, what caused the diabetes?"},{"time":62624,"text":"You see, diabetes is an autoimmune disease"},{"time":64477,"text":"where your body fights itself, and at the time people thought"},{"time":67852,"text":"that somehow maybe exposure to a pathogen"},{"time":70893,"text":"had triggered my immune system to fight the pathogen"},{"time":75365,"text":"and then kill the cells that make insulin."},{"time":77423,"text":"And this is what I thought for a long period of time,"},{"time":79733,"text":"and that's in fact what medicine and people have focused on quite a bit,"},{"time":83781,"text":"the microbes that do bad things."},{"time":86703,"text":"And that's where I need my assistant here now."},{"time":89771,"text":"You may recognize her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92209,"text":"So, I went yesterday, I apologize, I skipped a few of the talks,"},{"time":97889,"text":"and I went over to the National Academy of Sciences building,"},{"time":100130,"text":"and they sell toys, giant microbes."},{"time":105577,"text":"And here we go!"},{"time":108962,"text":"So you have caught flesh-eating disease if you caught that one."},{"time":113717,"text":"I gotta get back out my baseball ability here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118145,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121852,"text":"So, unfortunately or not surprisingly, most of the microbes"},{"time":128233,"text":"they sell at the National Academy building are pathogens."},{"time":131576,"text":"Everybody focuses on the things that kill us,"},{"time":134545,"text":"and that's what I was focusing on."},{"time":136192,"text":"And it turns out that we are covered in a cloud of microbes,"},{"time":140753,"text":"and those microbes actually do us good much of the time,"},{"time":145273,"text":"rather than killing us."},{"time":146393,"text":"And so, we've known about this for some period of time."},{"time":149584,"text":"People have used microscopes to look at the microbes that cover us,"},{"time":153161,"text":"I know you're not paying attention to me, but ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154953,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":157051,"text":"The microbes that cover us."},{"time":158993,"text":"And if you look at them in the microscope,"},{"time":162153,"text":"you can see that we actually have 10 times as many cells"},{"time":165557,"text":"of microbes on us as we have human cells."},{"time":169025,"text":"There's more mass in the microbes than the mass of our brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173776,"text":"We are literally a teeming ecosystem of microorganisms."},{"time":178097,"text":"And unfortunately, if you want to learn about the microorganisms,"},{"time":182697,"text":"just looking at them in a microscope is not sufficient."},{"time":184977,"text":"And so we just heard about the DNA sequencing."},{"time":187557,"text":"It turns out that one of the best ways to look at microbes"},{"time":190085,"text":"and to understand them is to look at their DNA."},{"time":192621,"text":"And that's what I've been doing for 20 years,"},{"time":194763,"text":"using DNA sequencing, collecting samples from various places,"},{"time":198645,"text":"including the human body, reading the DNA sequence"},{"time":201549,"text":"and then using that DNA sequencing to tell us about"},{"time":204169,"text":"the microbes that are in a particular place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206335,"text":"And what's amazing, when you use this technology,"},{"time":209198,"text":"for example, looking at humans, we're not just covered"},{"time":212358,"text":"in a sea of microbes."},{"time":213494,"text":"There are thousands upon thousands of different kinds of microbes on us."},{"time":218605,"text":"We have millions of genes of microbes in our human"},{"time":223958,"text":"microbiome covering us."},{"time":225605,"text":"And so this microbial diversity differs between people,"},{"time":229110,"text":"and what people have been thinking about in the last 10,"},{"time":232246,"text":"maybe 15 years is, maybe these microbes,"},{"time":235366,"text":"this microbial cloud in and on us,"},{"time":237414,"text":"and the variation between us, may be responsible"},{"time":241294,"text":"for some of the health and illness differences between us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244864,"text":"And that comes back to the diabetes story I was telling you."},{"time":247987,"text":"It turns out that people now think that one of the triggers"},{"time":251393,"text":"for type 1 diabetes is not fighting a pathogen,"},{"time":253774,"text":"but is in fact trying to -- miscommunicating with the microbes"},{"time":258165,"text":"that live in and on you."},{"time":259662,"text":"And somehow maybe the microbial community that's"},{"time":262366,"text":"in and on me got off, and then this triggered some sort"},{"time":266399,"text":"of immune response and led to me killing the cells"},{"time":268638,"text":"that make insulin in my body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270859,"text":"And so what I want to tell you about for a few minutes is,"},{"time":273955,"text":"what people have learned using DNA sequencing techniques"},{"time":277747,"text":"in particular, to study the microbial cloud"},{"time":281406,"text":"that lives in and on us."},{"time":282980,"text":"And I want to tell you a story about a personal project."},{"time":285444,"text":"My first personal experience with studying the microbes"},{"time":288238,"text":"on the human body actually came from a talk that I gave,"},{"time":292388,"text":"right around the corner from here at Georgetown."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294188,"text":"I gave a talk, and a family friend who happened to be"},{"time":297205,"text":"the Dean of Georgetown Medical School was at the talk,"},{"time":299748,"text":"and came up to me afterwards saying, they were doing"},{"time":302238,"text":"a study of ileal transplants in people."},{"time":305588,"text":"And they wanted to look at the microbes after the transplants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309564,"text":"And so I started a collaboration with this person,"},{"time":312628,"text":"Michael Zasloff and Thomas Fishbein, to look at the microbes"},{"time":315901,"text":"that colonized these ilea after they were transplanted into a recipient."},{"time":320374,"text":"And I can tell you all the details about the microbial study"},{"time":323516,"text":"that we did there, but the reason I want to tell you this story"},{"time":325766,"text":"is something really striking that they did at the beginning"},{"time":328990,"text":"of this project."},{"time":330013,"text":"They take the donor ileum, which is filled with microbes from a donor"},{"time":334378,"text":"and they have a recipient who might have a problem"},{"time":336661,"text":"with their microbial community, say Crohn's disease,"},{"time":339286,"text":"and they sterilized the donor ileum."},{"time":342846,"text":"Cleaned out all the microbes, and then put it in the recipient."},{"time":347141,"text":"They did this because this was common practice"},{"time":349805,"text":"in medicine, even though it was obvious"},{"time":352934,"text":"that this was not a good idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355072,"text":"And fortunately, in the course of this project,"},{"time":358077,"text":"the transplant surgeons and the other people"},{"time":360640,"text":"decided, forget common practice. We have to switch."},{"time":365061,"text":"So they actually switched to leaving some of the microbial"},{"time":369206,"text":"community in the ileum. They leave the microbes with the donor,"},{"time":373206,"text":"and theoretically that might help the people who are"},{"time":376782,"text":"receiving this ileal transplant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378871,"text":"And so, people -- this is a study that I did now."},{"time":382173,"text":"In the last few years there's been a great expansion"},{"time":384478,"text":"in using DNA technology to study the microbes in and on people."},{"time":388656,"text":"There's something called the Human Microbiome Project"},{"time":390464,"text":"that's going on in the United States,"},{"time":392320,"text":"and MetaHIT going on in Europe, and a lot of other projects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394854,"text":"And when people have done a variety of studies,"},{"time":398043,"text":"they have learned things such as, when a baby is"},{"time":401675,"text":"born, during vaginal delivery you get colonized by the"},{"time":404659,"text":"microbes from your mother."},{"time":405851,"text":"There are risk factors associated with cesarean sections,"},{"time":408907,"text":"some of those risk factors may be due to mis-colonization"},{"time":412938,"text":"when you carve a baby out of its mother"},{"time":415330,"text":"rather than being delivered through the birth canal."},{"time":418155,"text":"And a variety of other studies have shown that the"},{"time":421604,"text":"microbial community that lives in and on us"},{"time":423411,"text":"helps in development of the immune system,"},{"time":425674,"text":"helps in fighting off pathogens, helps in our metabolism,"},{"time":430619,"text":"and determining our metabolic rate, probably"},{"time":433699,"text":"determines our odor, and may even shape our behavior"},{"time":436874,"text":"in a variety of ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438810,"text":"And so, these studies have documented or suggested"},{"time":441866,"text":"out of a variety of important functions for the microbial community,"},{"time":446153,"text":"this cloud, the non-pathogens that live in and on us."},{"time":450690,"text":"And one area that I think is very interesting,"},{"time":454274,"text":"which many of you may have now that we've thrown"},{"time":456940,"text":"microbes into the crowd, is something that I would call \"germophobia.\""},{"time":460870,"text":"So people are really into cleanliness, right?"},{"time":463829,"text":"We have antibiotics in our kitchen counters,"},{"time":465808,"text":"people are washing every part of them all of the time,"},{"time":468904,"text":"we pump antibiotics into our food, into our communities,"},{"time":473930,"text":"we take antibiotics excessively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476371,"text":"And killing pathogens is a good thing if you're sick,"},{"time":480210,"text":"but we should understand that when we pump chemicals"},{"time":483474,"text":"and antibiotics into our world, that we're also killing"},{"time":486371,"text":"the cloud of microbes that live in and on us."},{"time":488666,"text":"And excessive use of antibiotics, in particular in children,"},{"time":491666,"text":"has been shown to be associated with, again, risk factors"},{"time":494895,"text":"for obesity, for autoimmune diseases, for a variety"},{"time":499151,"text":"of problems that are probably due to disruption"},{"time":501055,"text":"of the microbial community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504159,"text":"So the microbial community can go wrong"},{"time":507511,"text":"whether we want it to or not,"},{"time":509223,"text":"or we can kill it with antibiotics,"},{"time":511471,"text":"but what can we do to restore it?"},{"time":513567,"text":"I'm sure many people here have heard about probiotics."},{"time":516679,"text":"Probiotics are one thing that you can try and do to restore"},{"time":519687,"text":"the microbial community that is in and on you."},{"time":522111,"text":"And they definitely have been shown to be effective in some cases."},{"time":525583,"text":"There's a project going on at UC Davis where people are using"},{"time":528680,"text":"probiotics to try and treat, prevent,"},{"time":531575,"text":"necrotizing enterocolitis in premature infants."},{"time":534087,"text":"Premature infants have real problems with their microbial community."},{"time":537495,"text":"And it may be that probiotics can help prevent"},{"time":540015,"text":"the development of this horrible necrotizing enterocolitis"},{"time":543151,"text":"in these premature infants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544816,"text":"But probiotics are sort of a very, very simple solution."},{"time":548807,"text":"Most of the pills that you can take or the yogurts that you can eat"},{"time":552162,"text":"have one or two species in them, maybe five species in them,"},{"time":556949,"text":"and the human community is thousands upon thousands of species."},{"time":560615,"text":"So what can we do to restore our microbial community"},{"time":564543,"text":"when we have thousands and thousands of species on us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567742,"text":"Well, one thing that animals seem to do is,"},{"time":570448,"text":"they eat poo -- coprophagia."},{"time":574462,"text":"And it turns out that many veterinarians,"},{"time":579071,"text":"old school veterinarians in particular,"},{"time":581080,"text":"have been doing something called \"poo tea,\""},{"time":583796,"text":"not booty, but poo tea, to treat colic and other"},{"time":589601,"text":"ailments in horses and cows and things like that,"},{"time":593224,"text":"where you make tea from the poo from a healthy"},{"time":597172,"text":"individual animal and you feed it to a sick animal."},{"time":600321,"text":"Although, unless you have a fistulated cow with a big hole in its side,"},{"time":604761,"text":"and you can put your hand into its rumen,"},{"time":607300,"text":"it's hard to imagine that the delivery of microbes"},{"time":610708,"text":"directly into the mouth and through the entire"},{"time":613637,"text":"top of the digestive tract is the best delivery system,"},{"time":617285,"text":"so you may have heard in people they are now doing"},{"time":621405,"text":"fecal transplants, where rather than delivering"},{"time":626055,"text":"a couple of probiotic microbes through the mouth,"},{"time":628487,"text":"they are delivering a community of probiotics,"},{"time":631940,"text":"a community of microbes from a healthy donor,"},{"time":634420,"text":"through the other end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636557,"text":"And this has turned out to be very effective in fighting"},{"time":639887,"text":"certain intransigent infectious diseases"},{"time":642253,"text":"like Clostridium difficile infections that can stay"},{"time":646092,"text":"with people for years and years and years."},{"time":648189,"text":"Transplants of the feces, of the microbes from the feces,"},{"time":653052,"text":"from a healthy donor has actually been shown to cure"},{"time":655917,"text":"systemic C. dif infections in some people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658778,"text":"Now what these transplants, these fecal transplants, or"},{"time":664620,"text":"the poo tea suggest to me, and many other people"},{"time":669079,"text":"have come up with this same idea, is that"},{"time":670823,"text":"the microbial community in and on us, it's an organ."},{"time":674711,"text":"We should view it as a functioning organ, part of ourselves."},{"time":679718,"text":"We should treat it carefully and with respect,"},{"time":683709,"text":"and we do not want to mess with it, say by C-sections"},{"time":687689,"text":"or by antibiotics or excessive cleanliness,"},{"time":692597,"text":"without some real good justification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695814,"text":"And what the DNA sequencing technologies are allowing people to do now"},{"time":699454,"text":"is do detailed studies of, say, 100 patients who have Crohn's disease"},{"time":706406,"text":"and 100 people who don't have Crohn's disease."},{"time":708941,"text":"Or 100 people who took antibiotics when they were little,"},{"time":712774,"text":"and 100 people who did not take antibiotics."},{"time":715198,"text":"And we can now start to compare the community of microbes"},{"time":719278,"text":"and their genes and see if there are differences."},{"time":722581,"text":"And eventually we may be able to understand if they're not"},{"time":725983,"text":"just correlative differences, but causative."},{"time":728607,"text":"Studies in model systems like mouse and other animals"},{"time":732077,"text":"are also helping do this, but people are now using"},{"time":735286,"text":"these technologies because they've gotten very cheap,"},{"time":737590,"text":"to study the microbes in and on a variety of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741504,"text":"So, in wrapping up, what I want to tell you about is,"},{"time":746094,"text":"I didn't tell you a part of the story of coming down with diabetes."},{"time":749301,"text":"It turns out that my father was an M.D.,"},{"time":752065,"text":"actually studied hormones. I told him many times"},{"time":756537,"text":"that I was tired, thirsty, not feeling very good."},{"time":761327,"text":"And he shrugged it off, I think he either thought"},{"time":764206,"text":"I was just complaining a lot, or it was the typical"},{"time":767485,"text":"M.D. \"nothing can be wrong with my children.\""},{"time":770104,"text":"We even went to the International Society of Endocrinology"},{"time":773325,"text":"meeting as family in Quebec."},{"time":775455,"text":"And I was getting up every five minutes to pee,"},{"time":780949,"text":"and drinking everybody's water at the table,"},{"time":783384,"text":"and I think they all thought I was a druggie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786318,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":788038,"text":"But the reason I'm telling you this is that"},{"time":790014,"text":"the medical community, my father as an example,"},{"time":793014,"text":"sometimes doesn't see what's right in front of their eyes."},{"time":796581,"text":"The microbial cloud, it is right in front of us."},{"time":800566,"text":"We can't see it most of the time. It's invisible."},{"time":803366,"text":"They're microbes. They're tiny."},{"time":804837,"text":"But we can see them through their DNA,"},{"time":807789,"text":"we can see them through the effects that they have on people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811038,"text":"And what we need now"},{"time":812656,"text":"is to start thinking about this microbial community in the context"},{"time":816325,"text":"of everything in human medicine."},{"time":818838,"text":"It doesn't mean that it affects every part of us,"},{"time":821905,"text":"but it might."},{"time":823304,"text":"What we need is a full field guide to the microbes"},{"time":827229,"text":"that live in and on people, so that we can understand"},{"time":830622,"text":"what they're doing to our lives."},{"time":833894,"text":"We are them. They are us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836965,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838293,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}